                            <comment id="13163043" author="mbenson" created="Mon, 5 Dec 2011 21:09:05 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;I agree that Digester should have a centralized mechanism for resolving String to Class.  Maybe we should just import lang3.ClassUtils and shade it.  There are a number of things &lt;span class=&quot;error&quot;&gt;&amp;#91;digester&amp;#93;&lt;/span&gt; &quot;redoes&quot; from &lt;span class=&quot;error&quot;&gt;&amp;#91;lang&amp;#93;&lt;/span&gt;&apos;s repertoire IMO.  But as I&apos;m not a &quot;regular&quot; &lt;span class=&quot;error&quot;&gt;&amp;#91;digester&amp;#93;&lt;/span&gt; developer, I don&apos;t feel strongly about either approach.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
